it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface

Class OWLReferencesInterface.OWLReferencesContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface.OWLReferencesInterface.OWLReferencesContainer
  • Enclosing class:
    OWLReferencesInterface

    public static class OWLReferencesInterface.OWLReferencesContainer
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements methods to instantiate or retrieve a reference to an ontology. This is done by keeping track of all instances of the extending classes of OWLReferencesInterface in a static map (allReferences). The database maps each instance with respect to a name (ontoName) given when the reference was initialized as an unique ontology qualifier.
    Project: aMOR
    File: it.emarolab.amor.owlInterface.OWLReferences
    Licence: GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE. Version 3, 29 June 2007
    Author: Buoncompagni Luca (luca.buoncompagni@edu.unige.it)
    affiliation: DIBRIS, EMAROLab, University of Genoa.
    date: Feb 10, 2016

      • newOWLReferences

        public static OWLReferences newOWLReferences(java.lang.String referenceName,
                                             java.lang.String filePath,
                                             java.lang.String ontologyPath,
                                             java.lang.Boolean bufferingReasoner,
                                             java.lang.Integer command)
        Creates a new OWL References by calling OWLReferences.OWLReferences(String, String, String, Boolean, Integer)
        Parameters:
        referenceName - the unique identifier of this ontology references to store in allReferences.
        filePath - the file path (or URL) to the ontology.
        ontologyPath - the IRI path of the ontology.
        bufferingReasoner - if true, the reasoner is triggered only when OWLReferencesInterface.synchronizeReasoner() is called. Else, the reasoner is called after every change to the ontology.
        command - specifying if the ontology should be created, loaded from file or from web. Possible values are: COMMAND_CREATE, COMMAND_LOAD_FILE or COMMAND_LOAD_WEB.
        Returns:
        a fully initialised OWL Reference object.

      • newOWLReferences

        public static OWLReferences newOWLReferences(java.lang.String referenceName,
                                             java.lang.String filePath,
                                             java.lang.String ontologyPath,
                                             java.lang.String reasonerFactory,
                                             java.lang.Boolean bufferingReasoner,
                                             java.lang.Integer command)
        Creates a new OWL References by calling OWLReferences.OWLReferences(String, String, String, String, Boolean, Integer)
        Parameters:
        referenceName - the unique identifier of this ontology reference to store in allReferences.
        filePath - the file path (or URL) to the ontology.
        ontologyPath - the IRI path of the ontology.
        reasonerFactory - the reasoner factory qualifier referring to the reasoner to use. Possible values are: [OWLLibrary.REASONER_QUALIFIER_PELLET, OWLLibrary.REASONER_QUALIFIER_HERMIT, OWLLibrary.REASONER_QUALIFIER_SNOROCKET or OWLLibrary.REASONER_QUALIFIER_FACT].
        bufferingReasoner - if true, the reasoner is triggered only when OWLReferencesInterface.synchronizeReasoner() is called. Else, the reasoner is called after every change to the ontology.
        command - specifying if the ontology should be created, loaded from file or from web. Possible value of commands are: COMMAND_CREATE, COMMAND_LOAD_FILE or COMMAND_LOAD_WEB.
        Returns:
        a fully initialised OWL Reference object.
